  <prompt>
    Add `Tasks.ReadWrite` to the delegated scope list in `GraphClientFactory.cs` so OBO token acquisition includes it. Add an OBO smoke test asserting that `GraphServiceClient.Me.Todo.Lists.GetAsync()` succeeds with a test user's token. Measure BFF publish size and report delta vs. baseline (~45.65 MB).
  </prompt>

  <role>Spaarke BFF API developer with ASP.NET Core + Microsoft Graph SDK + OBO expertise.</role>

  <goal>`GraphClientFactory.cs` requests `Tasks.ReadWrite` in its delegated scopes. OBO smoke test passes against the target environment. BFF publish-size delta documented (expected ≈0 — no new packages, just config change).</goal>

  <context>
    <background>`GraphClientFactory` is the central OBO factory for all delegated Graph calls. Adding a scope here makes it available for the to-be-added `TodoGraphSyncHandler` and the webhook endpoint without introducing a new auth path.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/Graph/GraphClientFactory.cs</file>
      <file>tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Infrastructure/Graph/GraphClientFactoryTests.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Reuse existing OBO flow; do not introduce a new auth path.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API pattern for any new test-only endpoints (avoid in this task).</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF publish-size verification mandatory. Baseline ~45.65 MB; ceiling 60 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md §F">Test obligation: this task adds an OBO smoke test in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Infrastructure/Graph/`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
