    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read current `GraphClientFactory.cs` delegated-scopes list. Identify the registration point.</step>
    <step order="2">Add `"Tasks.ReadWrite"` to the scope list (alphabetical insertion).</step>
    <step order="3">Add an OBO smoke test in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Infrastructure/Graph/` that mocks the OBO token, calls `GraphServiceClient.Me.Todo.Lists.GetAsync()`, and asserts the configured scopes include `Tasks.ReadWrite`.</step>
    <step order="4">Run `dotnet build` and `dotnet test` for `Sprk.Bff.Api` projects. Verify clean.</step>
    <step order="5">Run BFF publish-size check: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed output; record delta vs. ~45.65 MB baseline in task completion report. Expected: ≈0 MB delta (config-only change).</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` on `Sprk.Bff.Api`. Confirm zero HIGH-severity CVEs (regression check).</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md status to ✅ completed.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build, test, publish, CVE scan</tool>
